snippet.title: 🎋 Bamboo Helped Her Survive! 🔥💪 #camping #survival #bushcraft #outdoors #lifehack
snippet.description:
Making fire with bamboo is a time-tested survival skill — and yes, it still works!

Here’s what you need to know:
✔ Use hard, dry bamboo — yellow or slightly green is best.
❌ Avoid gray bamboo — it’s been waterlogged and wears out too fast.
✔ A bit damp? Just dry it in the sun or wipe it down.
✔ Start rubbing slowly — it helps warm the surface and push out moisture.
✔ Sharper edges = better friction.
✔ Save your energy — once you smell burning, that’s your cue to speed up and press harder.
✔ Smoke doesn’t mean fire yet — keep going!
⚠️ Don’t forget to prepare a tinder nest in advance — once the ember forms, gently place it inside to blow it into flame.

For this process I used my ROXON S803E Elite multitool — super handy in the wild!
🛠️ Link in bio if you’re curious.

I did it — and so can you! 💪🔥
